{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "ECC"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Ecclesiastes \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["Ecclesiastes or, The Preacher \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Ecclesiastes \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Ecc \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Ecclesiastes \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt2", "content": ["or, The Preacher \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "ECC 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ECC 1:1"}, "The words of the Preacher, the son of Dawood, king in Jerusalem:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ECC 1:2"}, "\u201cVanity of vanities,\u201d says the Preacher; \u201cVanity of vanities, all is vanity.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ECC 1:3"}, "What does man gain from all his labour in which he labours under the sun?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ECC 1:4"}, "One generation goes, and another generation comes; but the earth remains forever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ECC 1:5"}, "The sun also rises, and the sun goes down, and hurries to its place where it rises.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ECC 1:6"}, "The wind goes towards the south, and turns around to the north. It turns around continually as it goes, and the wind\nreturns again to its courses. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ECC 1:7"}, "All the rivers run into the sea, yet the sea is not full. To the place where the rivers flow, there they flow again.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ECC 1:8"}, "All things are full of weariness beyond uttering. The eye is not satisfied with seeing, nor the ear filled with hearing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ECC 1:9"}, "That which has been is that which shall be; and that which has been done is that which shall be done: and there is no new\nthing under the sun. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ECC 1:10"}, "Is there a thing of which it may be said, \u201cBehold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:10\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as an\ninterjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " this is new?\u201d It has been long ago, in the ages which were before us.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ECC 1:11"}, "There is no memory of the former; neither shall there be any memory of the latter that are to come, amongst those that\nshall come after. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ECC 1:12"}, "I, the Preacher, was king over Israel in Jerusalem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ECC 1:13"}, "I applied my heart to seek and to search out by wisdom concerning all that is done under the sky. It is a heavy burden\nthat Allah", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:13 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d\n(Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " has given to the sons of men to be afflicted with. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ECC 1:14"}, "I have seen all the works that are done under the sun; and behold, all is vanity and a chasing after wind.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ECC 1:15"}, "That which is crooked can\u2019t be made straight; and that which is lacking can\u2019t be counted.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ECC 1:16"}, "I said to myself, \u201cBehold, I have obtained for myself great wisdom above all who were before me in Jerusalem. Yes, my\nheart has had great experience of wisdom and knowledge.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ECC 1:17"}, "I applied my heart to know wisdom, and to know madness and folly. I perceived that this also was a chasing after wind.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ECC 1:18"}, "For in much wisdom is much grief; and he who increases knowledge increases sorrow.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "ECC 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ECC 2:1"}, "I said in my heart, \u201cCome now, I will test you with mirth: therefore enjoy pleasure;\u201d and behold, this also was vanity.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ECC 2:2"}, "I said of laughter, \u201cIt is foolishness;\u201d and of mirth, \u201cWhat does it accomplish?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ECC 2:3"}, "I searched in my heart how to cheer my flesh with wine, my heart yet guiding me with wisdom, and how to lay hold of folly,\nuntil I might see what it was good for the sons of men that they should do under heaven all the days of their lives.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ECC 2:4"}, "I made myself great works. I built myself houses. I planted myself vineyards.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ECC 2:5"}, "I made myself gardens and parks, and I planted trees in them of all kinds of fruit.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ECC 2:6"}, "I made myself pools of water, to water from it the forest where trees were grown.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ECC 2:7"}, "I bought male servants and female servants, and had servants born in my house. I also had great possessions of herds and\nflocks, above all who were before me in Jerusalem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ECC 2:8"}, "I also gathered silver and gold for myself, and the treasure of kings and of the provinces. I got myself male and female\nsingers, and the delights of the sons of men: musical instruments, and that of all sorts.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ECC 2:9"}, "So I was great, and increased more than all who were before me in Jerusalem. My wisdom also remained with me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ECC 2:10"}, "Whatever my eyes desired, I didn\u2019t keep from them. I didn\u2019t withhold my heart from any joy, for my heart rejoiced because\nof all my labour, and this was my portion from all my labour. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ECC 2:11"}, "Then I looked at all the works that my hands had worked, and at the labour that I had laboured to do; and behold, all was\nvanity and a chasing after wind, and there was no profit under the sun.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ECC 2:12"}, "I turned myself to consider wisdom, madness, and folly; for what can the king\u2019s successor do? Just that which has been\ndone long ago. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ECC 2:13"}, "Then I saw that wisdom excels folly, as far as light excels darkness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ECC 2:14"}, "The wise man\u2019s eyes are in his head, and the fool walks in darkness\u2014and yet I perceived that one event happens to them\nall. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ECC 2:15"}, "Then I said in my heart, \u201cAs it happens to the fool, so will it happen even to me; and why was I then more wise?\u201d Then I\nsaid in my heart that this also is vanity. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ECC 2:16"}, "For of the wise man, even as of the fool, there is no memory forever, since in the days to come all will have been long\nforgotten. Indeed, the wise man must die just like the fool! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ECC 2:17"}, "So I hated life, because the work that is worked under the sun was grievous to me; for all is vanity and a chasing after\nwind. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ECC 2:18"}, "I hated all my labour in which I laboured under the sun, because I must leave it to the man who comes after me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ECC 2:19"}, "Who knows whether he will be a wise man or a fool? Yet he will have rule over all of my labour in which I have laboured,\nand in which I have shown myself wise under the sun. This also is vanity.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ECC 2:20"}, "Therefore I began to cause my heart to despair concerning all the labour in which I had laboured under the sun.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ECC 2:21"}, "For there is a man whose labour is with wisdom, with knowledge, and with skilfulness; yet he shall leave it for his\nportion to a man who has not laboured for it. This also is vanity and a great evil.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ECC 2:22"}, "For what does a man have of all his labour and of the striving of his heart, in which he labours under the sun?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ECC 2:23"}, "For all his days are sorrows, and his travail is grief; yes, even in the night his heart takes no rest. This also is\nvanity. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ECC 2:24"}, "There is nothing better for a man than that he should eat and drink, and make his soul enjoy good in his labour. This\nalso I saw, that it is from the hand of Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ECC 2:25"}, "For who can eat, or who can have enjoyment, more than I? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ECC 2:26"}, "For to the man who pleases him, Allah gives wisdom, knowledge, and joy; but to the sinner he gives travail, to gather and\nto heap up, that he may give to him who pleases Allah. This also is vanity and a chasing after wind.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "ECC 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ECC 3:1"}, "For everything there is a season, and a time for every purpose under heaven:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ECC 3:2"}, "a time to be born, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time to die; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["a time to plant, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time to pluck up that which is planted; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ECC 3:3"}, "a time to kill, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time to heal; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["a time to break down, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time to build up; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ECC 3:4"}, "a time to weep, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time to laugh; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["a time to mourn, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time to dance; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ECC 3:5"}, "a time to cast away stones, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time to gather stones together; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["a time to embrace, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time to refrain from embracing; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ECC 3:6"}, "a time to seek, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time to lose; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["a time to keep, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time to cast away; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ECC 3:7"}, "a time to tear, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time to sew; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["a time to keep silence, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time to speak; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ECC 3:8"}, "a time to love, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time to hate; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["a time for war, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a time for peace. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ECC 3:9"}, "What profit has he who works in that in which he labours? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ECC 3:10"}, "I have seen the burden which Allah has given to the sons of men to be afflicted with.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ECC 3:11"}, "He has made everything beautiful in its time. He has also set eternity in their hearts, yet so that man can\u2019t find out\nthe work that Allah has done from the beginning even to the end.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ECC 3:12"}, "I know that there is nothing better for them than to rejoice, and to do good as long as they live.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ECC 3:13"}, "Also that every man should eat and drink, and enjoy good in all his labour, is the gift of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ECC 3:14"}, "I know that whatever Allah does, it shall be forever. Nothing can be added to it, nor anything taken from it; and Allah\nhas done it, that men should fear before him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ECC 3:15"}, "That which is has been long ago, and that which is to be has been long ago. Allah seeks again that which is passed away.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ECC 3:16"}, "Moreover I saw under the sun, in the place of justice, that wickedness was there; and in the place of righteousness, that\nwickedness was there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ECC 3:17"}, "I said in my heart, \u201cAllah will judge the righteous and the wicked; for there is a time there for every purpose and for\nevery work.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ECC 3:18"}, "I said in my heart, \u201cAs for the sons of men, Allah tests them, so that they may see that they themselves are like\nanimals. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ECC 3:19"}, "For that which happens to the sons of men happens to animals. Even one thing happens to them. As the one dies, so the\nother dies. Yes, they have all one breath; and man has no advantage over the animals; for all is vanity.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ECC 3:20"}, "All go to one place. All are from the dust, and all turn to dust again.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ECC 3:21"}, "Who knows the spirit of man, whether it goes upward, and the spirit of the animal, whether it goes downward to the\nearth?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ECC 3:22"}, "Therefore I saw that there is nothing better than that a man should rejoice in his works; for that is his portion: for\nwho can bring him to see what will be after him? \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "ECC 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ECC 4:1"}, "Then I returned and saw all the oppressions that are done under the sun: and behold, the tears of those who were\noppressed, and they had no comforter; and on the side of their oppressors there was power; but they had no comforter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ECC 4:2"}, "Therefore I praised the dead who have been long dead more than the living who are yet alive.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ECC 4:3"}, "Yes, better than them both is him who has not yet been, who has not seen the evil work that is done under the sun.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ECC 4:4"}, "Then I saw all the labour and achievement that is the envy of a man\u2019s neighbour. This also is vanity and a striving after\nwind. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ECC 4:5"}, "The fool folds his hands together and ruins himself. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ECC 4:6"}, "Better is a handful, with quietness, than two handfuls with labour and chasing after wind.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ECC 4:7"}, "Then I returned and saw vanity under the sun. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ECC 4:8"}, "There is one who is alone, and he has neither son nor brother. There is no end to all of his labour, neither are his eyes\nsatisfied with wealth. \u201cFor whom then, do I labour and deprive my soul of enjoyment?\u201d This also is vanity. Yes, it is a\nmiserable business. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ECC 4:9"}, "Two are better than one, because they have a good reward for their labour.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ECC 4:10"}, "For if they fall, the one will lift up his fellow; but woe to him who is alone when he falls, and doesn\u2019t have another to\nlift him up. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ECC 4:11"}, "Again, if two lie together, then they have warmth; but how can one keep warm alone?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ECC 4:12"}, "If a man prevails against one who is alone, two shall withstand him; and a threefold cord is not quickly broken.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ECC 4:13"}, "Better is a poor and wise youth than an old and foolish king who doesn\u2019t know how to receive admonition any more.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ECC 4:14"}, "For out of prison he came out to be king; yes, even in his kingdom he was born poor.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ECC 4:15"}, "I saw all the living who walk under the sun, that they were with the youth, the other, who succeeded him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ECC 4:16"}, "There was no end of all the people, even of all them over whom he was\u2014yet those who come after shall not rejoice in him.\nSurely this also is vanity and a chasing after wind. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "ECC 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ECC 5:1"}, "Guard your steps when you go to Allah\u2019s house; for to draw near to listen is better than to give the sacrifice of fools,\nfor they don\u2019t know that they do evil. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ECC 5:2"}, "Don\u2019t be rash with your mouth, and don\u2019t let your heart be hasty to utter anything before Allah; for Allah is in heaven,\nand you on earth. Therefore let your words be few. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ECC 5:3"}, "For as a dream comes with a multitude of cares, so a fool\u2019s speech with a multitude of words.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ECC 5:4"}, "When you vow a vow to Allah, don\u2019t defer to pay it; for he has no pleasure in fools. Pay that which you vow.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ECC 5:5"}, "It is better that you should not vow, than that you should vow and not pay.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ECC 5:6"}, "Don\u2019t allow your mouth to lead you into sin. Don\u2019t protest before the messenger that this was a mistake. Why should Allah\nbe angry at your voice, and destroy the work of your hands? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ECC 5:7"}, "For in the multitude of dreams there are vanities, as well as in many words; but you must fear Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ECC 5:8"}, "If you see the oppression of the poor, and the violent taking away of justice and righteousness in a district, don\u2019t\nmarvel at the matter, for one official is eyed by a higher one, and there are officials over them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ECC 5:9"}, "Moreover the profit of the earth is for all. The king profits from the field.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ECC 5:10"}, "He who loves silver shall not be satisfied with silver; nor he who loves abundance, with increase: this also is vanity.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ECC 5:11"}, "When goods increase, those who eat them are increased; and what advantage is there to its owner, except to feast on them\nwith his eyes? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ECC 5:12"}, "The sleep of a labouring man is sweet, whether he eats little or much; but the abundance of the rich will not allow him\nto sleep. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ECC 5:13"}, "There is a grievous evil which I have seen under the sun: wealth kept by its owner to his harm.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ECC 5:14"}, "Those riches perish by misfortune, and if he has fathered a son, there is nothing in his hand.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ECC 5:15"}, "As he came out of his mother\u2019s womb, naked shall he go again as he came, and shall take nothing for his labour, which he\nmay carry away in his hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ECC 5:16"}, "This also is a grievous evil, that in all points as he came, so shall he go. And what profit does he have who labours for\nthe wind? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ECC 5:17"}, "All his days he also eats in darkness, he is frustrated, and has sickness and wrath.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ECC 5:18"}, "Behold, that which I have seen to be good and proper is for one to eat and to drink, and to enjoy good in all his labour,\nin which he labours under the sun, all the days of his life which Allah has given him; for this is his portion.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ECC 5:19"}, "Every man also to whom Allah has given riches and wealth, and has given him power to eat of it, and to take his portion,\nand to rejoice in his labour\u2014this is the gift of Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ECC 5:20"}, "For he shall not often reflect on the days of his life; because Allah occupies him with the joy of his heart.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "ECC 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ECC 6:1"}, "There is an evil which I have seen under the sun, and it is heavy on men:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ECC 6:2"}, "a man to whom Allah gives riches, wealth, and honour, so that he lacks nothing for his soul of all that he desires, yet\nAllah gives him no power to eat of it, but an alien eats it. This is vanity, and it is an evil disease.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ECC 6:3"}, "If a man fathers a hundred children, and lives many years, so that the days of his years are many, but his soul is not\nfilled with good, and moreover he has no burial; I say, that a stillborn child is better than he:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ECC 6:4"}, "for it comes in vanity, and departs in darkness, and its name is covered with darkness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ECC 6:5"}, "Moreover it has not seen the sun nor known it. This has rest rather than the other.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ECC 6:6"}, "Yes, though he live a thousand years twice told, and yet fails to enjoy good, don\u2019t all go to one place?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ECC 6:7"}, "All the labour of man is for his mouth, and yet the appetite is not filled.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ECC 6:8"}, "For what advantage has the wise more than the fool? What has the poor man, that knows how to walk before the living?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ECC 6:9"}, "Better is the sight of the eyes than the wandering of the desire. This also is vanity and a chasing after wind.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ECC 6:10"}, "Whatever has been, its name was given long ago; and it is known what man is; neither can he contend with him who is\nmightier than he. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ECC 6:11"}, "For there are many words that create vanity. What does that profit man?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ECC 6:12"}, "For who knows what is good for man in life, all the days of his vain life which he spends like a shadow? For who can tell\na man what will be after him under the sun? \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "ECC 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ECC 7:1"}, "A good name is better than fine perfume; and the day of death better than the day of one\u2019s birth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ECC 7:2"}, "It is better to go to the house of mourning than to go to the house of feasting; for that is the end of all men, and the\nliving should take this to heart. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ECC 7:3"}, "Sorrow is better than laughter; for by the sadness of the face the heart is made good.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ECC 7:4"}, "The heart of the wise is in the house of mourning; but the heart of fools is in the house of mirth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ECC 7:5"}, "It is better to hear the rebuke of the wise than for a man to hear the song of fools.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ECC 7:6"}, "For as the crackling of thorns under a pot, so is the laughter of the fool. This also is vanity.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ECC 7:7"}, "Surely extortion makes the wise man foolish; and a bribe destroys the understanding.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ECC 7:8"}, "Better is the end of a thing than its beginning. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The patient in spirit is better than the proud in spirit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ECC 7:9"}, "Don\u2019t be hasty in your spirit to be angry, for anger rests in the bosom of fools.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ECC 7:10"}, "Don\u2019t say, \u201cWhy were the former days better than these?\u201d For you do not ask wisely about this.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ECC 7:11"}, "Wisdom is as good as an inheritance. Yes, it is more excellent for those who see the sun.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ECC 7:12"}, "For wisdom is a defence, even as money is a defence; but the excellency of knowledge is that wisdom preserves the life of\nhim who has it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ECC 7:13"}, "Consider the work of Allah, for who can make that straight, which he has made crooked?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ECC 7:14"}, "In the day of prosperity be joyful, and in the day of adversity consider; yes, Allah has made the one side by side with\nthe other, to the end that man should not find out anything after him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ECC 7:15"}, "All this I have seen in my days of vanity: there is a righteous man who perishes in his righteousness, and there is a\nwicked man who lives long in his evildoing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ECC 7:16"}, "Don\u2019t be overly righteous, neither make yourself overly wise. Why should you destroy yourself?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ECC 7:17"}, "Don\u2019t be too wicked, neither be foolish. Why should you die before your time?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ECC 7:18"}, "It is good that you should take hold of this. Yes, also don\u2019t withdraw your hand from that; for he who fears Allah will\ncome out of them all. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ECC 7:19"}, "Wisdom is a strength to the wise man more than ten rulers who are in a city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ECC 7:20"}, "Surely there is not a righteous man on earth who does good and doesn\u2019t sin.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ECC 7:21"}, "Also don\u2019t take heed to all words that are spoken, lest you hear your servant curse you;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ECC 7:22"}, "for often your own heart knows that you yourself have likewise cursed others.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ECC 7:23"}, "All this I have proved in wisdom. I said, \u201cI will be wise;\u201d but it was far from me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ECC 7:24"}, "That which is, is far off and exceedingly deep. Who can find it out?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ECC 7:25"}, "I turned around, and my heart sought to know and to search out, and to seek wisdom and the scheme of things, and to know\nthat wickedness is stupidity, and that foolishness is madness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ECC 7:26"}, "I find more bitter than death the woman whose heart is snares and traps, whose hands are chains. Whoever pleases Allah\nshall escape from her; but the sinner will be ensnared by her. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ECC 7:27"}, "\u201cBehold, I have found this,\u201d says the Preacher, \u201cto one another, to find out the scheme\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ECC 7:28"}, "which my soul still seeks, but I have not found. I have found one man amongst a thousand, but I have not found a woman\namongst all those. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ECC 7:29"}, "Behold, I have only found this: that Allah made man upright; but they search for many schemes.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "ECC 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ECC 8:1"}, "Who is like the wise man? And who knows the interpretation of a thing? A man\u2019s wisdom makes his face shine, and the\nhardness of his face is changed. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ECC 8:2"}, "I say, \u201cKeep the king\u2019s command!\u201d because of the oath to Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ECC 8:3"}, "Don\u2019t be hasty to go out of his presence. Don\u2019t persist in an evil thing, for he does whatever pleases him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ECC 8:4"}, "for the king\u2019s word is supreme. Who can say to him, \u201cWhat are you doing?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ECC 8:5"}, "Whoever keeps the commandment shall not come to harm, and his wise heart will know the time and procedure.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ECC 8:6"}, "For there is a time and procedure for every purpose, although the misery of man is heavy on him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ECC 8:7"}, "For he doesn\u2019t know that which will be; for who can tell him how it will be?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ECC 8:8"}, "There is no man who has power over the spirit to contain the spirit; neither does he have power over the day of death.\nThere is no discharge in war; neither shall wickedness deliver those who practise it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ECC 8:9"}, "All this I have seen, and applied my mind to every work that is done under the sun. There is a time in which one man has\npower over another to his hurt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ECC 8:10"}, "So I saw the wicked buried. Indeed they came also from holiness. They went and were forgotten in the city where they did\nthis. This also is vanity. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ECC 8:11"}, "Because sentence against an evil work is not executed speedily, therefore the heart of the sons of men is fully set in\nthem to do evil. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ECC 8:12"}, "Though a sinner commits crimes a hundred times, and lives long, yet surely I know that it will be better with those who\nfear Allah, who are reverent before him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ECC 8:13"}, "But it shall not be well with the wicked, neither shall he lengthen days like a shadow, because he doesn\u2019t fear Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ECC 8:14"}, "There is a vanity which is done on the earth, that there are righteous men to whom it happens according to the work of\nthe wicked. Again, there are wicked men to whom it happens according to the work of the righteous. I said that this also is\nvanity. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ECC 8:15"}, "Then I commended mirth, because a man has no better thing under the sun, than to eat, and to drink, and to be joyful: for\nthat will accompany him in his labour all the days of his life which Allah has given him under the sun.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ECC 8:16"}, "When I applied my heart to know wisdom, and to see the business that is done on the earth (even though eyes see no sleep\nday or night), \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ECC 8:17"}, "then I saw all the work of Allah, that man can\u2019t find out the work that is done under the sun, because however much a man\nlabours to seek it out, yet he won\u2019t find it. Yes even though a wise man thinks he can comprehend it, he won\u2019t be able to find\nit. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "ECC 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ECC 9:1"}, "For all this I laid to my heart, even to explore all this: that the righteous, and the wise, and their works, are in the\nhand of Allah; whether it is love or hatred, man doesn\u2019t know it; all is before them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ECC 9:2"}, "All things come alike to all. There is one event to the righteous and to the wicked; to the good, to the clean, to the\nunclean, to him who sacrifices, and to him who doesn\u2019t sacrifice. As is the good, so is the sinner; he who takes an oath, as he\nwho fears an oath. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ECC 9:3"}, "This is an evil in all that is done under the sun, that there is one event to all: yes also, the heart of the sons of men\nis full of evil, and madness is in their heart while they live, and after that they go to the dead.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ECC 9:4"}, "For to him who is joined with all the living there is hope; for a living dog is better than a dead lion.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ECC 9:5"}, "For the living know that they will die, but the dead don\u2019t know anything, neither do they have any more a reward; for\ntheir memory is forgotten. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ECC 9:6"}, "Also their love, their hatred, and their envy has perished long ago; neither do they any longer have a portion forever in\nanything that is done under the sun. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ECC 9:7"}, "Go your way\u2014eat your bread with joy, and drink your wine with a merry heart; for Allah has already accepted your works.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ECC 9:8"}, "Let your garments be always white, and don\u2019t let your head lack oil.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ECC 9:9"}, "Live joyfully with the wife whom you love all the days of your life of vanity, which he has given you under the sun, all\nyour days of vanity, for that is your portion in life, and in your labour in which you labour under the sun.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ECC 9:10"}, "Whatever your hand finds to do, do it with your might; for there is no work, nor plan, nor knowledge, nor wisdom, in\nSheol,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " where you are going.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ECC 9:11"}, "I returned and saw under the sun that the race is not to the swift, nor the battle to the strong, neither yet bread to\nthe wise, nor yet riches to men of understanding, nor yet favour to men of skill; but time and chance happen to them all.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ECC 9:12"}, "For man also doesn\u2019t know his time. As the fish that are taken in an evil net, and as the birds that are caught in the\nsnare, even so are the sons of men snared in an evil time, when it falls suddenly on them.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ECC 9:13"}, "I have also seen wisdom under the sun in this way, and it seemed great to me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ECC 9:14"}, "There was a little city, and few men within it; and a great king came against it, besieged it, and built great bulwarks\nagainst it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ECC 9:15"}, "Now a poor wise man was found in it, and he by his wisdom delivered the city; yet no man remembered that same poor man.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ECC 9:16"}, "Then I said, \u201cWisdom is better than strength.\u201d Nevertheless the poor man\u2019s wisdom is despised, and his words are not\nheard. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ECC 9:17"}, "The words of the wise heard in quiet are better than the cry of him who rules amongst fools.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ECC 9:18"}, "Wisdom is better than weapons of war; but one sinner destroys much good.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "ECC 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ECC 10:1"}, "Dead flies cause the oil of the perfumer to produce an evil odour;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so does a little folly outweigh wisdom and honour. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ECC 10:2"}, "A wise man\u2019s heart is at his right hand, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but a fool\u2019s heart at his left. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ECC 10:3"}, "Yes also when the fool walks by the way, his understanding fails him, and he says to everyone that he is a fool.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ECC 10:4"}, "If the spirit of the ruler rises up against you, don\u2019t leave your place; for gentleness lays great offences to rest.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ECC 10:5"}, "There is an evil which I have seen under the sun, the sort of error which proceeds from the ruler.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ECC 10:6"}, "Folly is set in great dignity, and the rich sit in a low place.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ECC 10:7"}, "I have seen servants on horses, and princes walking like servants on the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ECC 10:8"}, "He who digs a pit may fall into it; and whoever breaks through a wall may be bitten by a snake.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ECC 10:9"}, "Whoever carves out stones may be injured by them. Whoever splits wood may be endangered by it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ECC 10:10"}, "If the axe is blunt, and one doesn\u2019t sharpen the edge, then he must use more strength; but skill brings success.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ECC 10:11"}, "If the snake bites before it is charmed, then is there no profit for the charmer\u2019s tongue.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ECC 10:12"}, "The words of a wise man\u2019s mouth are gracious; but a fool is swallowed by his own lips.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ECC 10:13"}, "The beginning of the words of his mouth is foolishness; and the end of his talk is mischievous madness.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ECC 10:14"}, "A fool also multiplies words. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Man doesn\u2019t know what will be; and that which will be after him, who can tell him?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ECC 10:15"}, "The labour of fools wearies every one of them; for he doesn\u2019t know how to go to the city.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ECC 10:16"}, "Woe to you, land, when your king is a child, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your princes eat in the morning! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ECC 10:17"}, "Happy are you, land, when your king is the son of nobles, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your princes eat in due season, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for strength, and not for drunkenness! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ECC 10:18"}, "By slothfulness the roof sinks in; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and through idleness of the hands the house leaks. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ECC 10:19"}, "A feast is made for laughter, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and wine makes the life glad; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and money is the answer for all things. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ECC 10:20"}, "Don\u2019t curse the king, no, not in your thoughts; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and don\u2019t curse the rich in your bedroom: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for a bird of the sky may carry your voice, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and that which has wings may tell the matter. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "ECC 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ECC 11:1"}, "Cast your bread on the waters; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for you shall find it after many days. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ECC 11:2"}, "Give a portion to seven, yes, even to eight; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for you don\u2019t know what evil will be on the earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ECC 11:3"}, "If the clouds are full of rain, they empty themselves on the earth;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and if a tree falls towards the south, or towards the north,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["in the place where the tree falls, there shall it be. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ECC 11:4"}, "He who observes the wind won\u2019t sow; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he who regards the clouds won\u2019t reap. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ECC 11:5"}, "As you don\u2019t know what is the way of the wind, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor how the bones grow in the womb of her who is with child;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even so you don\u2019t know the work of Allah who does all. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ECC 11:6"}, "In the morning sow your seed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and in the evening don\u2019t withhold your hand; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for you don\u2019t know which will prosper, whether this or that,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or whether they both will be equally good. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ECC 11:7"}, "Truly the light is sweet, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and it is a pleasant thing for the eyes to see the sun. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ECC 11:8"}, "Yes, if a man lives many years, let him rejoice in them all;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but let him remember the days of darkness, for they shall be many.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["All that comes is vanity. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ECC 11:9"}, "Rejoice, young man, in your youth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and let your heart cheer you in the days of your youth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and walk in the ways of your heart, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and in the sight of your eyes; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but know that for all these things Allah will bring you into judgement.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ECC 11:10"}, "Therefore remove sorrow from your heart, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and put away evil from your flesh; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for youth and the dawn of life are vanity. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "ECC 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ECC 12:1"}, "Remember also your Creator in the days of your youth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["before the evil days come, and the years draw near, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["when you will say, \u201cI have no pleasure in them;\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ECC 12:2"}, "Before the sun, the light, the moon, and the stars are darkened,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the clouds return after the rain; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ECC 12:3"}, "in the day when the keepers of the house shall tremble, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the strong men shall bow themselves, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the grinders cease because they are few, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and those who look out of the windows are darkened, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ECC 12:4"}, "and the doors shall be shut in the street; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["when the sound of the grinding is low, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and one shall rise up at the voice of a bird, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all the daughters of music shall be brought low; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ECC 12:5"}, "yes, they shall be afraid of heights, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and terrors will be on the way; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the almond tree shall blossom, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the grasshopper shall be a burden, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and desire shall fail; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because man goes to his everlasting home, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the mourners go about the streets: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ECC 12:6"}, "before the silver cord is severed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or the golden bowl is broken, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or the pitcher is broken at the spring, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or the wheel broken at the cistern, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ECC 12:7"}, "and the dust returns to the earth as it was, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the spirit returns to Allah who gave it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ECC 12:8"}, "\u201cVanity of vanities,\u201d says the Preacher. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cAll is vanity!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ECC 12:9"}, "Further, because the Preacher was wise, he still taught the people knowledge. Yes, he pondered, sought out, and set in\norder many proverbs. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ECC 12:10"}, "The Preacher sought to find out acceptable words, and that which was written blamelessly, words of truth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ECC 12:11"}, "The words of the wise are like goads; and like nails well fastened are words from the masters of assemblies, which are\ngiven from one shepherd. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ECC 12:12"}, "Furthermore, my son, be admonished: of making many books there is no end; and much study is a weariness of the flesh.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ECC 12:13"}, "This is the end of the matter. All has been heard. Fear Allah and keep his commandments; for this is the whole duty of\nman. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ECC 12:14"}, "For Allah will bring every work into judgement, with every hidden thing, whether it is good, or whether it is evil.\n"]}]}